# Before acting — hilavitkutin invariants

Re-check these before every write or code change. The build
pipeline will reject violations; catching them here saves a cycle.

- `#![no_std]` in every crate. No `alloc`, no `Vec`, no `String`,
  no `Box`, no `extern crate alloc;`.
- Monomorphisation is the dispatch. No `dyn`, no `TypeId`, no
  `std::any`. WorkUnits are generic over their `AccessSet`.
- Static composition only. No `inventory::`, no `#[ctor]`, no
  `#[distributed_slice]`, no runtime plugin registration.
- Pre-allocated thread pool. No `thread::spawn`, `tokio::spawn`,
  `async_std::spawn` at runtime.
- Canonical vocabulary: `pipeline`, `phase`, `waist`, `trunk`,
  `fiber`, `branch`, `bridge`, `morsel`, `micro-morsel`, `entry`,
  `record`. Dead terms (do not introduce): `chain`, `chain_group`,
  `partition`, `archetype`, `entity`, `row`, `order`.
- `hilavitkutin-api` is contract-only; never let it depend on
  `hilavitkutin` engine internals.
- `hilavitkutin-build` is build-dep only; no runtime linkage.
- Edit templates in `mock/agent/`, not generated files under
  `.claude/` or `.github/`.
- Use `cargo mock` state-machine subcommands for `design_rounds/`
  transitions. Never hand-rename `.lock.md` / `.deprecated.md`
  suffixes.
